reviewText:
This was awesome. There isn't tons of action (definately not "non-stop" like the cover says...) but what there is, is great. Actually I mostly want to be a big idiot and point out the delicate theme they sometimes play is by William Shakespeare, from Twelth Night. (nasal hnnn)
The words are:
  What is love? 'tis not hereafter;
 Present mirth hath present laughter;
 What's to come is still unsure:
 In delay there lies no plenty;
 Then come kiss me, sweet and twenty,
 Youth's a stuff will not endure.
How's that for unhelpful? Anyways, if you like manga-movies, this is alot of fun.
(& though I rented this, I'm thinking of picking up a copy...)
